ise that develops and commercializes technology and manages laboratories for government customers headquartered in columbus ohio battelle has a vast science and technology reach battelle with the national labs it manages or comanages oversees  staff members and conducts  billion in annual research and development it counts as its successes the development of the xerox machine pioneering work on the compact disc and medical technology innovations in the area of commercial innovation battelle has spawned new ventures and companies in fiber optics pharmaceuticals energy electronics and informatics battelle also manages or comanages five of the us national laboratories for the department of energy – brookhaven national laboratory oak ridge national laboratory pacific northwest national laboratory and national renewable energy laboratory and most recently idaho national laboratory martin joined battelle in october  after a year career with ford motor company most recently as group vice presidentbusiness strategy martin played a key role in ford’s global governance and strategy and in championing diversity and talent development processes during his tenure at ford he held several key positions chief financial officergroup vice president headford north american and corporate vice president presidentford south american and corporate vice president headglobal product and business strategy and corporate vice president in addition martin held posts in ford lio hotaiwan and ford europeessex england martin earned his ba in business economics with honors from strathclyde university in glasgow scotland martin currently serves on the boards of directors for brookhaven science associates llc utbattelle llc and carpenter technology corporation a leading manufacturer and distributor of specialist alloys and engineered products martin is a member of the conference board council of cfos not who youre looking for find other martin inglis on spoke contact telephone email background report